

Don't worry. It doesn't hurt yet.

His eyes grew even wider.

That's not good.

Come on. I said as I helped him up.

Steve came over and gabbed Bucky's other arm. A medical plane was awaiting us as we reached outside. I helped Bucky to a stretcher right before Steve grabbed my arm and pulled me into a huge hug. Then he picked me up and put me on a stretcher. Nurses and doctors swarmed around me.
She is in shock! Someone said.

A mask was placed over my face. A shot was injected into my arm. Then the pain hit like a jolt. My eyes rolled back and I slipped into darkness.

